A '''centered pentachoric number''' is a [[figurate number]] that represents a [[pentachoron]].

The first such numbers are: 1, 6, 21, 56, 126, 251, 456, 771, 1231, 1876, 2751, 3906, 5396, 7281, … {{OEIS|id=A008498}}.

Centered pentachoric numbers can also be represented as the sum of the first n [[pentatope number]]s.

