In [[mathematics]], a  '''Lorentz surface''' is a [[surface (topology)|two-dimensional]] [[oriented manifold|oriented]] [[smooth manifold]] with a [[conformal equivalence]] class of [[Lorentzian metric]]s. It is the analogue of a [[Riemann surface]] in [[metric signature|indefinite signature]].

